I swear, EA / 2k are gonna force games outlets to change their review policies
"If there are any significant, read ANTI-CONSUMER, changes to a game after launch, we will change our reviews to reflect this change, accordingly."
2K games just added unskippable ads to 2K21 a month after launch.  0 heads up or notice.
Black Ops 4 added loot boxes / battle passes / all kinds of microtransactions to the game after 6 months
The latest MMA game from EA did the same thing, where they snuck in unskippable ads more than a month after launch.
Games companies are doing this shit to avoid the, rightfully, negative press they'd get if this shit was in the game at launch.
They hold off on it, let the reviews go out, make sure no more outlets are reviewing the game, or will change their reviews, THEN do it.
Late enough to avoid backlash, and late enough where if people are going to buy the game, they probably did.
Konami became a slot machine company, all the industry wants now is titles that print money.
The bean counters have taken over.  Art has no place in BUSINESS.  Nevermind that that art is how they got to where they are >_>
